'''Greg Hildebrandt''' ([[January 23]], [[1930s|1939]] - [[October 31]], [[2020#2024|2024]])<ref name="FacebookDeath" /> was an artist who commonly worked with his twin brother, [[Tim Hildebrandt]]. Together, they are usually known as the '''Brothers Hildebrandt'''. They are perhaps best known for their design of one of the earliest theatrical release posters for [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'']] in 1977.

Greg differed from his identical twin brother by growing moustache and beard.<ref name="gathering">''[[The Secrets of Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire]]'', Part 5: Shadow Play, I. GATHERING OF THE TRIBES</ref>

==Biography==
[[File:Star_Wars_Style_B_poster_1977.jpg|thumb|left|250px|The Hildebrandts' artwork for the ''Style B'' poster for the UK release of ''Star Wars'' (1977)]]
In 1977 the Hildebrandt brothers were approached by [[20th Century Studios|20th Century Fox]] to produce poster art for the British release of ''Star Wars'', only ten days before the opening.<ref name="gathering" /> A promotional poster had already been produced in US by the artist [[Tom Jung]], but Fox executives considered this poster "too dark". The twins had to work to a very tight deadline, and worked together in shifts to produce a finished product in 36 hours. Their version of the poster, referred to as ''Style B'', was distributed to be used on British cinema billboards for the UK release, and became possibly their best known work. Using the same layout as Jung's [[:File:Star Wars Style A poster 1977.jpg|''Style A'' poster]], it depicts [[Luke Skywalker]] standing in a heroic pose brandishing a shining [[lightsaber]] above his head, with [[Leia Skywalker Organa Solo|Princess Leia]] standing below him, and a large, ghostly image of [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader's]] helmet looming behind them. The central figures are surrounded by smaller depictions of other characters and a montage of [[starfighter]]s in combat amid a sea of stars. Both Jung and the Hildebrandts had worked on their posters without reference to photographs of the actual cast, and Fox and Lucasfilm subsequently decided that they wanted to promote the new film with a less stylised and more realistic depiction of the lead characters. Producer [[Gary Kurtz]] commissioned the film poster artist [[Tom Chantrell]] to paint a new version from film stills and publicity photos. Star Wars opened in British theatres on 28 November 1977, and the Hildebrandts' poster was displayed in UK cinemas for about two months before it was replaced by Chantrell's Style C poster.<ref name="filmschoolrejects">{{WebCite|url=https://filmschoolrejects.com/star-wars-the-posters-14ad09654325|text=The History of Star Wars Posters|author=William Dass|date=2016-12-14|work=[[Wikipedia:Film School Rejects|''Film School Rejects'']]|archivedate=20200807144518}}</ref><ref name="scifimovieposters">{{WebCite|url=http://www.sci-fimovieposters.co.uk/british-star-wars-posters.htm|text=A short history of the first British Star Wars posters|work=[http://www.sci-fimovieposters.co.uk Sci-Fi Movie Posters Shop]|archivedate=20200807211137}}</ref><!-- Paragraphs is likely to not be sourced properly -->

The Hildebrandts were present at the [[Wikipedia:San Diego Comic-Con|San Diego Comic-Con]] [[1995]], marking their return to the ''Star Wars'' universe, with the illustration of a cover for [[Star Wars Galaxy Magazine 5|''Star Wars Galaxy Magazine'' 5]] and the [[1996 Topps Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire|1996 Topps ''Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire'']] series of trading cards, part of the ''[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire]]'' multimedia project.<ref name="gathering" /> His children [[Gregory Hildebrandt Jr.|Gregory]] and [[Mary Hildebrandt]], and his daughter-in-law [[Olga Hildebrandt|Olga]], posed in various production photos for the card set.<ref>''[[Star Wars: The Art of the Brothers Hildebrandt]]''</ref>

During the ''Shadows'' project, the brothers visited [[LucasArts]], where [[Jon Knoles]] demonstrated for them the [[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (video game)|video game adaptation]].<ref>''[[The Secrets of Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire]]''</ref>

